                <p><br><br><br><br></p>
                <p style="text-align:right; font-size:30px; background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);">
                In 1999, the CubeSat was first introduced when Bob Twigs and Jordi Purig-Surai introduced a satellite blueprint to allow graduate students to develop and test small, low cost spacecraft in low earth orbit. Since then the idea of a low cost space exploration method has become increasingly popular propagating CubeSat development in the professional market.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>

